e humanity’: placement officers in Germany between social work and social policy -- tConclusion: social work and the making of social policy – lessons learned -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aBringing together international case studies, this book offers theoretical and empirical insights into the interaction between social work and social policy. Moving beyond existing studies on policy practice, the book employs the policy cycle as a core analytical frame and focuses on the influence of social work(ers) in the problem definition, agenda setting, policy formulation and implementation of social policy. Twenty-three contributors offer examples of policy making from seven different countries and demonstrate how social work practitioners can become political actors, while also encouraging policy makers to become aware of the potential of social work for the social policy-making process.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aSocial policy. 0aSocial service. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aAlfandari, Ravit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBranco, Francisco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastiñeira, Sergio Sánchez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD’Emilione, Matteo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeely, Megan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGal, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiuliano, Giovannina Assunta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGottwald, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.go